\"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports_Bay_Area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports_Bay_Area\"}, {\"begin\": 3056, \"end\": 3075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports_Bay_Area\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC Sports Bay Area\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports_Bay_Area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports_Bay_Area\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic basketball play\", \"from\": 3109, \"to\": 3132}, {\"ngram\": \"play\", \"from\": 3136, \"to\": 3140}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He will be working his sixth Olympics for NBCUniversal, previously calling basketball at the 2012 London Olympics and the Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 3142, \"to\": 3279, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3184, \"end\": 3196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 0.9999242483962245, \"rank\": 7.575734246641134e-05, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his sixth Olympics\", \"from\": 3161, \"to\": 3179}, {\"ngram\": \"basketball\", \"from\": 3217, \"to\": 3227}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2012 London Olympics\", \"from\": 3231, \"to\": 3255}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 3260, \"to\": 3278}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following is a closer look at this summer's NBC Olympics basketball team: Dwyane Wade \\u00b7 Naismith Basketball Hall of Famer, three-time NBA champion, Olympic gold medalist, 13-time NBA All-Star, eight-time All-NBA selection, and member of the NBA's 75th Anniversary Team \\u00b7 First Olympic assignment with NBC Sports; previously worked as a studio analyst for TNT's coverage of the NBA from 2019-2022 \\u00b7 Co-owner of the NBA's Utah Jazz, WNBA's Chicago Sky, MLS's Real Salt Lake, and NWSL's Utah Royals \\u00b7 ProducedThe Redeem Team, the Sports Emmy-winning 2008 U.S. Olympic Men's Basketball team documentary LaChina Robinson \\u00b7 Third Olympic assignment for NBC Sports \\u00b7 Host and basketball analyst for ESPN, working on NCAA Tournament, Women's Final Four, WNBA Playoffs, Finals, and Draft \\u00b7 Served as an analyst for Team USA Women's Basketball at Tokyo Olympics (filling in for Kara Lawson while she was coaching 3x3 basketball) Noah Eagle \\u00b7 2ndOlympics with NBC Sports, previously handling play-by-play for 3x3 basketball at the Tokyo Olympics \\u00b7 Play-by-play voice ofBig Ten Saturday Night \\u00b7 Called NFL Playoff game for NBC Sports and Big Ten basketball on Peacock last season \\u00b7 Last week, won Sports Emmy for Outstanding Personality/Emerging On Air Zora Stephenson \\u00b7 2ndOlympics with NBC Sports, previously serving as social media host during the 2022 Beijing Olympics \\u00b7 Sideline reporter for Notre Dame Football and Big Ten Football and as a play-by-play voice for Big Ten Women's Basketball on Peacock \\u00b7 Served as a sideline reporter for the Milwaukee Bucks on Bally Sports/Fox Sports Wisconsin from 2019-2023, and became the first woman to handle play-by-play for a Bucks game; covered the 2021 NBA championship team Kerith Burke \\u00b7 3rdOlympics with NBC Sports and second Olympic basketball assignment: served as sideline reporter for Team USA women's basketball games at the 2016 Rio Olympics; reported from Team USA's friends and family resort in Orlando, Fla., during the Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 3281, \"to\": 5285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3325, \"end\": 3337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}, {\"begin\": 3417, \"end\"